==Trivia==
[[File:Mandarin prison 2.PNG|thumb|250px|Slattery's tattoo on the back of his neck]]
*Slattery has a tattoo of [[Captain America's Shield]] on his neck, but in place of the star is the "A" symbol for anarchy.
*The ring on Slattery's right pinkie is the same one [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]] wears in ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]''.
*[[Aldrich Killian]]'s hiring of Trevor Slattery to impersonate the [[Mandarin]] is similar to the plot of the 1988 film ''{{WPS|Without a Clue}}'', which stars [[Ben Kingsley]]. In the film, Kingsley portrays {{WPS|Doctor Watson}}, who solves crimes as a hobby. To keep attention away from his medical career, he invents the fictional {{WPS|Sherlock Holmes}} and hires an alcoholic, dim-witted actor named Reginald Kincaid ({{WPS|Michael Caine}}) to pretend to be him.
*Some of Slattery's roles in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] reference [[Ben Kingsley]]'s real roles, such as his portrayal of {{WPS|Edgar Allan Poe}} in ''{{WPS|Omnibus (British TV programme)|Omnibus}}'', William Snow in ''{{WPS|Turtle Diary}}'', and Ron Jenkins in ''{{WPS|Coronation Street}}''.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Anthony Mackie]] originally auditioned for the role of Trevor Slattery in ''[[Iron Man 3]]''. While [[Ben Kingsley]] ultimately got the part, Mackie's positive screen test attracted the attention of [[Nate Moore]] and [[Joe Russo]], who decided to cast him as [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] in ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]''.<ref>[https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a28120934/anthony-mackie-falcon-captain-america-marvel/ ANTHONY MACKIE IS YOUR NEW CAPTAIN, AMERICA]</ref>
*Slattery was originally slated to die during the [[Battle on the Norco|Battle on the ''Norco'']] by injecting himself with [[Extremis]] to get back at [[Aldrich Killian]] only to blow himself up, with [[Drew Pearce]] describing the scene as "the most ''{{WPS|Monty Python}}'' of all of the beats" in the film. However, it was decided during the editing process to keep Slattery alive, leading to his arrest scene being shot during reshoots.<ref>[https://collider.com/drew-pearce-all-hail-the-king-runaways-movie-interview/ Drew Pearce Talks about His Marvel One-Shot ALL HAIL THE KING, Working with Marvel, NO HEROICS, the RUNAWAYS Movie, and More]</ref>
*[[Anthony Means Jefferson]], [[Tony Lynch]], [[Brett Metter]] and [[Josh Fried]] were stunt doubles for [[Ben Kingsley]] in the role of Trevor Slattery.
*[[Pete Flores]] and [[Ian Brugnoli]] were stand-ins for [[Ben Kingsley]] in the role of Trevor Slattery.

